# 📖 About This Repository

I created this repository while learning **Data Visualization** as a BCA (AI) student.

Instead of writing scattered notes, I decided to organize everything into a structured handbook that covers both theory and practical implementation.

The goal of this repository is to help beginners understand Data Visualization from scratch using simple explanations, Python code, real-world examples, and interview-oriented notes.

---

# 🎯 Objectives

- Learn Data Visualization from beginner to advanced level.
- Understand when and why each chart should be used.
- Master Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly, and Cufflinks.
- Practice with real datasets.
- Build mini projects.
- Prepare for Data Analyst interviews.

